    "output": "{\"content\": \"{\\n  \\\"status_reasoning\\\": {\\n    \\\"determined_status\\\": \\\"degraded\\\",\\n    \\\"status_justification\\\": [\\n      \\\"All 16 pods in namespace sock-shop are in Running phase and Ready, so the application is broadly up.\\\",\\n      \\\"Events show repeated Unhealthy startup probe failures for carts-6b5d88f967-9f5ch (timeouts and connection refused on /health), indicating a recent or intermittent readiness issue.\\\",\\n      \\\"A flash-agent pod (flash-agent-768c8f4599-bstdd) is present with non-standard labels (app=flash-agent) and has had at least one restart, suggesting an injected/auxiliary agent rather than a core sock-shop component.\\\",\\n      \\\"Metrics-server (pods.metrics.k8s.io) access is forbidden for this MCP service account, and Prometheus query tools are unavailable, so resource health cannot be quantitatively verified.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"data_quality\\\": {\\n      \\\"completeness\\\": \\\"partial\\\",\\n      \\\"gaps\\\": [\\n        \\\"metrics_unavailable\\\",\\n        \\\"events_truncated\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"confidence_impact\\\": \\\"Health score capped due to missing observability\\\"\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"thoughts\\\": {\\n    \\\"key_observations\\\": [\\n      \\\"Namespace sock-shop currently has 16 pods, all in Running status and reporting Ready (e.g., carts, catalogue, orders, payment, shipping, user, their DBs, front-end, queue-master, rabbitmq, plus kubernetes-mcp-server, prometheus-mcp-server, and flash-agent).\\\",\\n      \\\"Kubernetes events for sock-shop are predominantly Normal (Scheduled, Pulled, Created, Started, ScalingReplicaSet), indicating successful scheduling and startup for most workloads.\\\",\\n      \\\"There are Warning events for carts-6b5d88f967-9f5ch with Reason=Unhealthy, specifically startup probe failures against http://10.244.1.137:80/health (context deadline exceeded and connection refused). These appear to have occurred shortly after deployment and may have since cleared, as the pod is now Running and Ready.\\\",\\n      \\\"A flash-agent pod (flash-agent-768c8f4599-bstdd) exists in the namespace, with 2/2 containers Running and at least one restart. Its app label (app=flash-agent) and image (agentcert-flash-agent) suggest an external agent or chaos/validation component rather than a core microservice.\\\",\\n      \\\"Access to pods.metrics.k8s.io is forbidden for the MCP service account, and Prometheus query tools (execute_query, list_metrics) are not available, so CPU/memory/network metrics and chaos-related metrics cannot be inspected.\\\",\\n      \\\"No events with Reasons containing Inject, Kill, Chaos, Disrupt, or Fault are visible in the provided (truncated) events output.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"analysis_approach\\\": [\\n      \\\"Listed all pods in namespace sock-shop using a namespace-scoped pod listing tool to establish fleet composition and basic status.\\\",\\n      \\\"Listed events scoped to namespace sock-shop to identify scheduling issues, probe failures, or explicit disturbance/chaos markers.\\\",\\n      \\\"Attempted to retrieve per-pod resource metrics via pods_top with namespace=sock-shop; this failed due to RBAC (metrics.k8s.io forbidden).\\\",\\n      \\\"Attempted to fall back to Prometheus-based metrics via execute_query and to discover chaos-related metrics via list_metrics; both tools are unavailable in this MCP environment.\\\",\\n      \\\"Assessed potential chaos/external disturbance by: (a) scanning for unusual pods (flash-agent), (b) reviewing events for disturbance-related Reasons. Metric-backed disturbance detection was not possible due to missing tools.\\\",\\n      \\\"Synthesized health status based on pod phases/readiness, events (especially probe failures), and the presence of auxiliary/agent pods, while explicitly accounting for observability gaps.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"observability_gaps\\\": [\\n      \\\"functions.pods_top: forbidden to list pod metrics in 